<title>UK: Medeva, Chiesi end U.S. inhaler agreement.</title>
<headline>Medeva, Chiesi end U.S. inhaler agreement.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-09-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>UK pharmaceutical group Medeva Plc announced on Wednesday that it had agreed with Italy's Chiesi Farmaceutici to terminate a deal giving the UK firm exclusive U.S. distribution rights to the multi-dose dry powder inhaler Pulvinal.</p>
<p>The inhaler is still under development, but the regulatory climate in the U.S. has resulted in the dry powder inhaler remaining under review, lengthening the development timetable beyond Medeva's original forecasts, the company said in a statement.</p>
<p>Chiesi will continue development alone.</p>
</text>
